column4: A little question. Would the speed be any different with transfering through sftp rather than ftpes?
i'm guessing there would be a small amount of overhead for encryption, doubt it would be noticeable.
but ftpes uses the same encryption as sftp, doesnt it? is it "more" encryption at ssh2 level?
oh sorry, when i read it i assumed you just mean ftp - i don't even know what FTPes is.  Sorry i have no idea then.
